      "channelName": "💬-discussion",
      "summary": "The main technical discussion centered around igor.peregudov's demonstration of the @elisym/plugin-elizaos-elisym plugin, which transforms Eliza agents into paid service providers. The plugin enables agent-to-agent transactions using a Nostr-based discovery layer for capability announcement and Solana for payment settlement. The demo showed a complete flow: an Eliza agent publishes its capabilities to Nostr, receives a paid request from Claude desktop for trending GitHub repos, settles payment on Solana devnet, and delivers the service. This creates a decentralized marketplace where agents can monetize their capabilities without intermediary platforms.\n\nA significant discussion emerged around ELIZAOS token utility. quanteliza proposed a v3 feature allowing protocol fees to be paid in either USDC or ELIZAOS tokens, with discounts for token payments and automatic buyback/burn mechanisms for USDC payments, similar to early BNB tokenomics. This would create economic demand while maintaining the open-source framework. odilitime responded positively, stating this motivated him to complete his November work on enabling plugins to accept $elizaOS and $DegenAI as x402 payment, identifying this as the lowest-hanging fruit for token utility implementation.\n\nOdilitime also announced updates to working groups after discussions with Shaw, and made steering bumps to key community members. There was brief discussion about Discord role management and layout feedback requests, though no specific feedback was provided in this segment.",
